High-school beauty Umaru seems like the perfect teen wunderkind, but she's hiding a shocking double life. As soon as she gets home, she becomes a junk-food-inhaling, soda-guzzling, video-game-addicted slob. The only one who sees this unsavory side of Umaru is her beleaguered older brother Taihei, who does his best to keep up with his work while trying to get his little sister to behave like a decent member of society. As she makes new friends and gets into a number of wacky situations, Umaru will continue to fight for her right to stay up all night binging potato chips and anime. (Source: Anime News Network)

A new sister work from the same team that authored My wife is from a thousand years ago! If you could go back in time, what would you do?

I would wait for you at the school gate, wait there every day, and relentlessly pursue you until I win you over. What about you?

Hmm... I would wait patiently until I turn twenty-four to meet you again, then proceed step-by-step with dating, marriage, and then I can ask you this question again. I'm proceeding cautiously because I'm afraid the butterfly effect will cause me to lose you." (Source: Bilibili, translated)

After being put on trial, the deity once known as "The Divine Twilight" is offered a job by Thanatos, king of the underworld! Now, the fallen deity is back on Earth as his former self, Lee Chang-Seon, and is tasked with sealing those trying to invade from beyond. With the promise of a fresh start, Chang-Seon is gathering the gear and skills needed to get the job done, but he's feeling some watchful eyes on him... Will this Divine Twilight see a new day, or is the sun setting on his second chance?
(Source: Tapas, edited)

The story begins when the gods call a convention to decide whether to let humanity live or die, and settle on destroying humanity. But a lone valkyrie puts forward a suggestion to let the gods and humanity fight one last battle, as a last hope for humanity's continued survival. 13 gods will fight against 13 human champions in one-on-one battles to decide whether humanity lives or dies.

In a world where the Han Empire never fell, martial arts is a power used to squeeze people dry. So when a new continent is discovered, both good and evil men alike flee to settle there and escape the tyranny of the Emperor, opening up the era of a Martial Wild West.
In the turbulent frontier, Zhang Qian is a man that reincarnated from our cushy, modern world, but his new world is nothing like the fantastical world he dreamed about from reading martial arts novels. While the martial arts in his new world are powerful, they are also too crude and lack elegance. And so Qian journeys along the continent for his dream of bringing true martial arts back to the new realm.
(Source: Naver, translated)
Wo Jia Laopo Lai Zi Yiqian Nian Qian
Comedy, Fantasy, Romance, Slice of Life

Jiang He, a girl from the Tang Dynasty, jumped a thousand years into the future and appeared in front of Xu Qing. The love that spanned a thousand years brought them together as if by fate. Everything she knew had become ancient history. Relatives, friends, and enemies have all been left 1,200 years in the past. The boy will do anything to help this girl start a new life. Pain, confusion, cheers, and laughter will be made anew in the modern world.
(Source: Tencent, translated)
